# AEIOU AI - Windsurf Workspace Rules

## Project Context
- **Name**: AEIOU AI - Business Assistant
- **Stack**: Next.js 15 + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
- **Backend**: Django REST API
- **Database**: PostgreSQL

## Code Quality Standards

### TypeScript
- Use strict TypeScript configuration
- Explicit return types on exported functions
- No `any` types without justification comment
- Use interface over type for object definitions

### React/Next.js
- Use Server Components by default
- Add "use client" only for client-only behavior
- Use Next.js App Router patterns
- Implement proper loading and error states

### Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes
- Follow slate/indigo color scheme (not gray/blue)
- Use `className` patterns from shadcn/ui
- Mobile-first responsive design

### API Integration
- All API calls go through `/lib/api.ts`
- Use proper error handling with try/catch
- Implement loading states for async operations

### File Organization
- Components in `/components`
- Pages in `/app` (Next.js App Router)
- Utilities in `/lib`
- Types in `/types`

## Prohibited Patterns
- ❌ No inline styles (use Tailwind)
- ❌ No `console.log` in production code (use proper logging)
- ❌ No unhandled Promise rejections
- ❌ No hardcoded URLs (use env vars)
- ❌ No magic numbers (use constants)

## Required Patterns
- ✅ All forms must have validation
- ✅ All API endpoints must handle errors
- ✅ All user actions must have loading states
- ✅ All images must have alt text
- ✅ All buttons must be accessible (keyboard nav)

## Memory Usage
- Keep conversations focused on the task
- Use skills for specialized tasks (design, review, docs)
- Reference existing code patterns
- Follow the established color scheme (slate/indigo)

